The UnifiedRoster is looking great, but we need to improve the UX for the "Raids" tab.

Currently, the `raid_summary` is a single concatenated string ("Voidspire 5/6 H | Dreamrift 1/1 H"), which doesn't look great in the UI. Also, when viewing the "Raids" tab, columns like "Ilvl", "M+ Runs", "Audit", and "Access / Status" are unnecessary and clutter the screen.

Please refactor the following:

### 1. Backend (`CompiledRosterMemberDTO.php` & `RosterCompilerService.php`)
- Change the type of `raid_summary` in the DTO from `?string` to `array`.
- In the compiler, instead of imploding the instances with ` | `, return an array of formatted strings (e.g., `["Voidspire 5/6 H", "Dreamrift 1/1 H"]`). Return an empty array `[]` if there is no raid data.

### 2. Frontend (`UnifiedRoster.vue`)
- **Column Visibility:** Use `v-if` on both the `<th>` headers and the corresponding `<td>` cells for "M+ Runs", "Audit", and "Access / Status" so they are HIDDEN when the active tab is 'raids' (e.g., `v-if="activeTab !== 'raids'"`).
- **Raid Summary Rendering:** Render the new `raid_summary` array. Instead of plain text, loop through the array and render each raid as a distinct, styled Tailwind badge stacked vertically or flex-wrapped (e.g., `<div class="flex flex-col gap-1 items-center"><span class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs" v-for="...">...</span></div>`). Ensure this looks good for both main and alt rows.

Output ONLY the updated PHP files (`CompiledRosterMemberDTO`, `RosterCompilerService`) and the updated Vue template/script (`UnifiedRoster.vue`).
